{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Nationality, Immigration and Asylum Act |type = Act |parliament = |long_title = |year = 2002 |citation = |introduced_by = |territorial_extent = |si_made_date = |si_laid_date = |royal_assent = 7 November 2002 |commencement = |repeal_date = |replaces = |primary_legislation = |eu_directives = |amendments = |related_legislation = |repealing_legislation= |status = |original_text = |legislation_history = |use_new_UK-LEG = yes |UK-LEG_title = |revised_text = |theyworkforyou = |millbankhansard = }}
The '''Nationality, Immigration and Asylum Act 2002''' (c. 41) is an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]. It received [[royal assent]] on 7 November 2002.
Among other changes, the Act instituted the [[Life in the United Kingdom test]] for everyone seeking naturalisation or permanent residence in the UK.
